snippet.textDisplay: My meal to go to is Mexican-inspired wraps: union, bake it, a chopped courgette (or sweet pepper, or whatever vedge you like), bake it, add pealed tomatoes (1 can - or go all out and chop 3-4 tomatoes), 1 can of mexican beans, 1 can of corn, and herbs: oregano, paprika, cumin, little bit of cinnamon, amount of chili to your taste, and salt. Put it on some wraps with some creme fraiche and you're good to go, I generally eat 2-3 days from it. It's veggie, and without the creme fraiche (or a vegan variant), it's even vegan, and it's cheap.
